ZH: 这艘船沉入了海底。
EN: The ship sank to the bottom of the sea.

ZH: 这些石头沉入了水中。
EN: These stones sank into the water.

ZH: 他的帽子沉入了悬崖下的深渊。
EN: His hat plunged into the deep abyss below the cliff.

ZH: 这个寶石沉入了泥里。
EN: The gem sank into the mud.

ZH: 被囚禁的人将沉入幽闭的黑暗。
EN: The imprisoned person would sink into the confined darkness.

ZH: 我的沉入思考中，没有注意到周围的事情。
EN: I was so absorbed in my thoughts that I didn't pay attention to my surroundings.

ZH: 年久失修的古庙沉入地面。
EN: The ancient temple, which had not been maintained for a long time, sank into the ground.

ZH: 他的愧疚感沉入了心底。
EN: His sense of guilt sank deep into his heart.

ZH: 这种烦恼很容易沉入人的内心。
EN: This kind of worry can easily sink into a person's heart.

ZH: 那只浮漂沉入了水中。
EN: The floating buoy sank into the water.

ZH: 这位画家的作品沉入了历史的长河中。
EN: The works of this painter have sunk into the river of history.

ZH: 他试图把那段悲伤的往事沉入遗忘之中。
EN: He tried to bury that sad past deep in forgetfulness.

ZH: 这个城市沉入了黑暗，没有一点光亮。
EN: The city sank into darkness, without any light.

ZH: 他的身体沉入了黑夜之中，令人忧虑。
EN: His figure disappeared into the darkness, causing concern.

ZH: 他被问题所困扰，沉入苦思中。
EN: He was troubled by the problem and sank into contemplation.

ZH: 在这个漩涡中，所有声音都沉入了寂静之中。
EN: In this whirlpool, all voices sank into silence.

ZH: 对于他来说，工作是最好的沉入方式，可以暂时忘却所有烦恼。
EN: For him, work is the best way to immerse himself and temporarily forget all worries.

ZH: 那个岛屿沉入了大海的怀抱中。
EN: The island disappeared into the arms of the sea.

ZH: 这个想法逐渐沉入了我的心头。
EN: This idea gradually sank into my mind.

ZH: 音乐的美妙旋律使我沉入了幸福的境界。
EN: The beautiful melody of the music plunged me into a state of happiness.

ZH: 这个秘密很快沉入了历史的尘埃中。
EN: This secret soon sank into the dust of history.
